name: Blame It On The Sun
author: Stevie Wonder
lyrics:
Where has my love gone?  How can I go on?
 It seems dear love has gone away.
 Where is my spirit?  I'm nowhere near it.
 Oh yes, my love has gone astray.
But I'll blame it on the sun, the sun that didn't shine.
I'll blame it on the wind    and the trees.
I'll blame it on the time, that never was enough.
I'll blame it on the tide and the sea.
But, my heart blames it on me.
 Who poured the love out?  What made this bitter doubt?
 Is peace not here for me to see?
 Wish I could tell you, how I am feeling.
 But, words won't come for me to speak.
But I'll blame it on the sun, that didn't fill the sky.
I'll blame it on the birds and the trees.
I'll blame it on the day, that ended once too soon, 
I'll blame it on the nights that could not be.
But, my heart blames it on me. (Yeah, yeah, yeah, ooh).
(Your heart blames it on you this time).

name: Whiskey Heaven
author: Fats Domino
lyrics:
Every afternoon when I wake up,
I say a little prayer and I drink up,
and thank the lord for driving me home...
once more.
There's an open Bible on the table,
and an empty bottle on the floor.
Last night I thought I'd died,
and went...to Whiskey Heaven.
You know the sun never shines in Whiskey Heaven.
It rains Jack Daniels all the time.
There's a price you have to pay, hangovers every day,
flyin' high with honkey tonk Angels...in Whiskey Heaven.
There's a run down bar, open all night,
where me and my friends can get tight,
underneath the neon lights...in Whiskey Heaven. 
Well, we drink a little beer and wine,
we stay drunk most of the time,
we're always raisin' hell all night...
in Whiskey Heaven.
